SANTAFE DE BOGOTA , September 10 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- During the International Seminar on Criminology being held in Cartagena of Colombia , several American countries have agreed to take steps to prevent money laundering and to unravel financial networks established by drug-trafficking groups .
One step will be investigating the financial accounts of drug cartels and the diverse ways in which they launder money , said a spokesman .
Colombia will participate directly in the prosecution and the investigation to locate bank accounts of drug traffickers and other illegal operations .
Representatives of the 13 countries are attending the seminar began September 8 in the tourist zone of Cartagena de Indias , 200 kilometers north of Santa Fe de Bogota , the Colombian capital .
